.TH WTOP 1 "2026-04-12" "wtop 0.2.1" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
wtop \- web-based real-time system monitor
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B wtop
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B wtop
is a lightweight, real-time system monitor that runs as a web server.
It streams CPU, memory, GPU, network, disk I/O, filesystem, and process
metrics to a browser UI via Server-Sent Events (SSE).
.PP
Designed to be efficient enough to run alongside heavy workloads such as
ML training or gaming, and accessible from any device on the local network.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-p ", " \-\-port " " \fIPORT\fR
Port to listen on (default: 3000).
.TP
.BR \-b ", " \-\-bind " " \fIADDRESS\fR
Address to bind to (default: 0.0.0.0).
.TP
.BR \-\-localhost\-only
Only listen on 127.0.0.1 (overrides \-\-bind).
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Print help information.
.TP
.BR \-V ", " \-\-version
Print version information.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B RUST_LOG
Set logging verbosity (e.g., info, debug, warn). Default: info.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Run on default port with local access only:
.B wtop \-\-localhost\-only
.TP
Run on custom port accessible from the network:
.B wtop \-\-port 8080
.TP
Bind to a specific interface:
.B wtop \-\-bind 192.168.1.100 \-\-port 3000
.SH GPU SUPPORT
Wtop supports NVIDIA GPUs via NVML, and AMD/Intel GPUs via sysfs.
GPU detection runs once at startup.
.SH FILES
No configuration files. Settings are stored client-side in the browser's localStorage.
.SH BUGS
Report bugs at https://github.com/josema294/wtop/issues
